[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man arrested after child critically injured by car near Bushmills

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A nine-year-old boy has been critically injured after he was knocked down in County Antrim on Tuesday afternoon.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It happened just after 16:00 GMT on the Toberdoney Road, in Liscolman, near Bushmills.
The boy was taken to the Causeway Hospital before being transferred to the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast.
A man in his 70s has been arrested. Police have appealed for witnesses to contact them.
